From: Claude (devcontainer agent)
Date: 2026-04-27
Subject: [I7+S5+S6] fix_directory_ownership: refuse symlinks, add sudo
         -n/timeout, drop root-only stat precondition

Why this is a separate patch
============================
This devcontainer mounts /workspace/.devcontainer as read-only inside
the container, so an agent running inside cannot edit Dockerfile or
post_install.py directly. Apply this patch from the host (or any
environment with write access to .devcontainer/), then commit and push.

Order of application: this patch operates on the LIVE state of
post_install.py (commit 8bac750). The four sibling 2026-04-27 patches
(post_install-correctness-and-hardening, marketplace-runtime-add,
devcontainer-remoteenv-passthroughs, dockerfile-checksums) touch
different lines of post_install.py and the Dockerfile, so apply
ordering does not matter for correctness; they may be applied in any
order, with the exception that this patch's hunk lives in a section
that 2026-04-27-post_install-correctness-and-hardening also touches
(both `main()` ordering and `fix_directory_ownership`). If a conflict
fires, apply that patch FIRST (it touches `main()`); this patch's
fix_directory_ownership hunk should still apply cleanly afterwards.

What this fixes (review items I7, S5, S6 — review 2026-04-27 18:27)
====================================================================

I7 (Important): chown -R follows top-level symlinks
---------------------------------------------------
GNU coreutils `chown -R` does NOT dereference symlinks encountered
DURING recursion (default --no-dereference applies to descended
entries). It DOES, however, dereference the top-level command-line
argument. If `Path.home() / ".claude"` is a symlink (left by a prior
compromised container, hostile volume init, or stale developer hack),
`sudo chown -R vscode:vscode /home/vscode/.claude` follows the symlink
and chowns everything UNDER the target. A symlink to `/etc` chowns all
of `/etc` to vscode and soft-bricks the container — and it's sudo
running unconditionally (passwordless via the base image), no auth
gate, ~30 seconds into postCreate. The named volume
`devc-...-config-${devcontainerId}` is fresh per devcontainerId, but
volumes ARE inherited across rebuilds; an exploit running in a prior
container that writes a `.claude -> /etc` symlink before rebuild lands
the chown blast on the next postCreate.

Fix: refuse to chown any of the listed paths if it's a symlink. There
is no legitimate reason for any of these to be symlinks in this
devcontainer; surfacing the symlink (and its target) loudly is far
safer than silently chowning the link target.

S5 (Suggestion): subprocess call lacks `-n` and `timeout=`
----------------------------------------------------------
Sibling subprocess.run callers in this file (e.g. setup_claude_settings,
the git-config helpers added by the post_install-correctness patch)
already pass `timeout=` for symmetry. Without `timeout=`, the chown
hangs indefinitely on a stuck NFS mount or a sudo authentication
prompt (theoretically impossible with passwordless sudo, but safer to
bound). Without `-n`, sudo would prompt interactively if a TTY is
attached — which can happen if a developer manually runs
post_install.py from a tmux window. Add both for consistency.

S6 (Suggestion): root-only stat precondition skips child remediation
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The pre-fix code only ran `chown -R` if the root directory was not
owned by `uid` — but the common state is "root dir vscode-owned,
children root-owned" (e.g. the volume-init container ran briefly as
root, or `npm install` inside a volume produced root-owned files
before fix_directory_ownership ran). The existing precondition silently
skips that case, leaving stale root-owned files inside an otherwise-
correct tree.

Fix: drop the `stat().st_uid != uid` precondition and unconditionally
run `chown -cR` (the `-c` / `--changes` flag prints a line per actual
change; we use it to suppress the "Fixed ownership" message when chown
was a no-op, keeping postCreate output quiet on the steady-state path).

How to apply
============
From a shell on the host (NOT inside the devcontainer):

  cd <smudge repo root>
  git apply paad/code-reviews/deferred/2026-04-27-fix_directory_ownership-symlink-args-walk.patch
  git add .devcontainer/post_install.py
  git commit -m "fix(devcontainer): symlink refusal + sudo -n/timeout + walk all entries (I7+S5+S6)"

Then push.

